This paper analyzes the impact of biomedical papers on social media platforms, specifically Twitter and Mendeley. The analysis involves measuring altmetrics, which are a new kind of research impact metrics. This topic falls under several arXiv CS sub-categories, including digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and economic systems (cs.SOC), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). However, given the focus on altmetrics and scholarly literature, cs.DL and cs.SI are the most likely sub-categories.
